Workers replaced carpet at the Dome of the Rock with carpet paid for by King Abdullah II of Jordan  . 
  Scholars say the flooring could reveal clues to where the Ark of the Covenant was buried 2,500 years ago . 
  But Muslim authority in charge of Judaism's holiest site says the work was carried out 'behind their backs' They are angry they did not get the chance to document the ancient floor designs . 
  Jewish tradition says the gold-cased Ark is buried under the Dome . 
 